      emergencies. From a Latin American perspective, they consider it necessary
      to formulate a critical understanding rooted in alternative forms of
      perception and ways of experiencing nature, a sentiment shared by other
      artists. The concept of the non-human encourages the construction of
      alternative possible worlds, challenging ecocidal, economic,
      epistemological, and symbolic models that alarmingly threaten life and
      ecosystems.
    </p>
